snippet.textDisplay:
The reason these comparisons to other diseases are foolish is that coronavirus is incredibly more dangerous, because it is so insidiously infectious. It can easily reach pandemic level due to a 2 week asymptomatic period during which you show no symptoms and go about your daily life, but are still fully contagious and spread it, starting more people on a 2 week asymptomatic period, etc.

And where you have a pandemic, you have strained resources.
It's one thing to get something severe like Ebola or mad cow, but corona can infect tons of people, which eventually leads to too many people, not enough space to keep them to treat them. Which is also why you've seen such a fatality rate in China, and why the fatality rate is likely much higher than reported. An entire city of 11 million people is afflicted. Hospitals are at their breaking point, as are staff. And when that happens, people die because they cannot get treatment.

Also it is totally justified to blame China for this, as we now know this started possibly some time in NOVEMBER, and the ccp suppressed it, and punished doctors who tried to bring attention to it. They enabled it to reach pandemic level, during the Chinese New Year holiday at that, when there's tons of travel, and only took action when they literally could not ignore it anymore. All the while you have the WHO In China's pocket for some reason, also downplaying the danger of corona, until they also cannot ignore it, when instead everyone involved should have declared an emergency to begin with, instead of calling suspended travel and enforcing travel bans as excessive and fearmongering, for such a dangerously infectious virus.
